D. Not understanding cultural differences -> b

Which of the following sentences best reflects the you-viewpoint?
A. You'll like RiverCity Bank's location and services
B. Make RiverCity your bank
C. To get the service you need and the respect you deserve, bank D. with River City Bank
D. Bank with RiverCity Bank, the friendliest bank in town! -> c

Identify the one item that is not a method for improving your nonverbal communication (A)
A. Expect business professionals to share the same attitudes toward time
B. Pay close attention to your vocal characteristics
C. Maintain the eye contact your audience expects
D. Use touch only when appropriate -> a

Tasha Gibbs, a clerk at Memories and More, must notify Alec Preble that the crystal vase he ordered as a gift for his grandmother on her 70th birthday arrived with a crack in the base. Tasha has ordered a replacement vase, but it won't be delivered before Alec leaves for Grandma Preble's party. What method should Tasha use to convey her message?
A. E-mail
B. Telephone call
C. Memo
D. Letter -> b

A communicator's status within an organization has the greatest influence in
A. Grapevine communication
B. Horizontal communication
C. Network communication
D. Vertical communication -> d

Culture should be considered as part of which audience analysis element
A. Attitudes
B. Emotional Reaction
C. Interests
D. Knowledge -> a

Which of the following is NOT a barrier to effective listening?
A. Focusing on the content of the message
B. Listening selectively
C. Prejudgment
D. Lack of common ground -> b

Which of the following is NOT a step in the proofreading process
A. Read the material to a colleague bottom to top
B. Use your word processing software spell checker to check for spelling errors
C. Pay special attention to names, numbers, and unusual words
D. Read the material once for content, once for mechanics -> a

The casual or informal way in which English is used is known as
A. Conversation
B. Slang
C. Colloquial language
D. denotation -> c

The most important goal of business communication is that the receiver understands the message as the sender intends.
A. True
B. False -> A

Five generally recognized core cultural dimensions are
A. Corporate, multicultural, language, ethnicity, and global
B. Ethnicity, race, gender, age, and physical challenge
C. Friends, colleagues, employers, employees, and family
D. English, German, Scandinavian, French, and Japanese. -> b

Strategies for effective global communication include
A. Communicating by telephone instead of e-mail or postal mail
B. Using a translator when speaking to a person whose English is a second...
C. Learning about other cultures and applying what you learn.
D. Avoiding use of any words in a language other than your own to avoid.... -> c

Cultural barriers that may prohibit effective multicultural communication include
A. Discrimination and harassment, language, cultural relativism, and ethnocentrism
B. Quid pro pro, high-context culture, and the acceptance of the needs of others.
C. Stereotypes, hostile environment, and a common business language
D. Cultural relativism, ethnocentrism, and a knowledge of your own culture. -> a

When you do not need immediate feedback, which of these media is most effective? (A)
A. Oral
B. Electronic
C. All are equality effective
D. Written -> a

Unlike journalistic or creative writing, business writing is
A. Topical
B. Structured
C. Transactional
D. Brief -> c

The phrase "talking a mile a minute" is an example of a/an
A. Idiom
B. Denotation
C. Metaphor
D. Inference -> a

The sender and receiver have equal responsibility for achieving the goals of business communication
A. True
B. False -> b

In most business letters, the shortest paragraphs are.
A. The middle paragraphs
B. Both (the middle paragraphs) and (the paragraphs with the most detail about the topic)
C. The paragraphs with the most detail about the topic
D. The first and last paragraphs -> d

Strong verbs that express action and specific nouns that create a visual mind image are sometimes called
A. Strong or power words
B. Negative words
C. Redundant words
D. Obsolete words -> a

The greeting stage of a conversation
A. Previews what will follow
B. Provides information about your relationship with the receiver
C. May be either direct or indirect
D. Makes your position on the topic clear -> b

The revising process includes all but which one of the following?
A. Checking to see that business communication principles have been applied
B. Thinking about the visual image the message creates
C. Verifying the content for accuracy and completeness
D. Determining whether the message is mechanically correct -> d

Why are short subject lines desirable in e-mail?
A. Long subject lines duplicate too much of the message
B. They are easier to write than long subject lines.
C. Subject lines waste the writer's time because readers don't use them
D. A long subject line could be truncated by the receiver's e-mail system -> d

The sender analyzes the receiver's knowledge so that the sender can
A. Choose the approach to use in the message
B. Avoid making a negative impression
C. Emphasize receiver benefits
D. Compose the message at the proper level -> d

To emphasize the formality of a message, which of these media would be most effective?(B)
A. A blog post
B. An email
C. A printed memo
D. A fax -> b

Which of the following is not a form of nonverbal communication?
A. Mnemonics
B. Touching behavior
C. Vocal characteristics
D. Gesture and posture -> a

Which of the following is not a disadvantage of electronic media?
A. Potential for inadvertently creating tension and conflict
B. Prevention of speedy feedback
C. All of the above
D. Tendency for employees to overuse them -> b

Which of the following is a disadvantage of instant messaging?
A. Teamwork and work flow are improved.
B. Files and links to websites may be shared by users.
C. Messages are maintained on servers controlled by the provider.
D.Spontaneous interaction in real time is possible. -> c

The goal of outlining your content is to ensure that you
A. Include at least some specific evidence that doesn't support your main idea.
B. Cover the most important details, in the most logical and effective way
C. None of the above
D. Provide your audience with as many minor supporting points as you can think of -> b

Written media include which of the following?
A. Charts, graphs, diagrams
B. Teleconferencing
C. All of the above
D. Letters, memos, and reports -> d

Effective listeners engage in all of the following except
A. Interrupting when they disagree
B. Making eye contact with the speaker.
C. Giving the speaker nonverbal cues.
D. Looking for opportunities to learn. -> a

Examples of communication challenges in a global environment are
A. All of the above
B. Differences in time
C. Words that have different meanings and connotations and different language patterns for part of speech
D. Not understanding cultural differences. -> a

The planning stage should take about
A. 30% of time you have to produce the message.
B. 70% of time you have to produce the message.
C. 50% of the time you have to produce the message.
D. 10% of time you have to produce the message. -> c

